result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffery C. Denton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Interfere w/Fire Fighting-Alarm/Fighters, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.12(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 14CF138, 14CF197, & 14CM371 2:10 pm cases called. Defendant Jeffery C Denton in court with attorney Ryan S. Ulrich.  Steven P. Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement/argued sentence.   Court addresses preliminary hearing in 14CF138. Defendant wishes to waive the right to a preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of right to preliminary hearing, has read the complaint, finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Ulrich confirms receipt, waives formal reading. Defedant enters No Contest plea to Count 1. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1 of 14CF138. No Contest to Count 1 of 14CM371.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 2, 3, 4, 5 in 14CF138, Count 2 in 14CM371 and 14CF197. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Ulrich. Court sentences the defendant to each: 5 months WCJ, without Huber but with Good Time Credit. Credit for 45 days served. Restitution of $197.18 to Waushara County Sheriff's Department and $171.66 on 14CM371. Court directs restitution be paid out of bond posted. Court orders costs to be paid through bond posted, balance to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given.
Plea/sentencing hearing on January 15, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
